    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lede">How Cert Happens handles quiz sessions, correction reports, analytics, and service-provider data.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="page-shell legal-page prose">
    <p class="legal-page__updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 22, 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Cert Happens does not require an account to use its practice tests. We aim to
      collect only the information needed to operate the site, protect it from abuse,
      understand general site performance, and improve question quality.
    </p>

    <h2>Practice-test sessions</h2>
    <p>
      Your active test, question order, displayed answer order, selections, flags,
      and completion state are stored in your browser's session storage. This
      information remains in the current browser tab so that moving between questions
      or refreshing the page does not erase the test.
    </p>
    <p>
      Session data is not automatically sent to Cert Happens merely because you take
      or complete a test.
    </p>

    <h2>Question reports</h2>
    <p>
      When you submit a question report, the site stores information needed to review
      the issue. This can include the question ID, exam and test identifiers, report
      category, optional note, displayed answer order, selected answer identifiers,
      source page, data version, and submission date.
    </p>
    <p>
      Reports do not require your name or email address. Cert Happens does not store
      your IP address in the question-report database, although infrastructure
      providers may process network information temporarily to provide security and
      deliver the service.
    </p>

    <h2>Cloudflare services</h2>
    <p>
      The site uses Cloudflare for hosting, content delivery, security, Turnstile
      verification, and database services. Cloudflare may process technical request
      information as part of providing those services.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      Cert Happens may use Cloudflare Web Analytics to understand aggregate page
      traffic and performance. The purpose is to learn which pages are useful and
      whether the site performs well, not to build individual visitor profiles.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising and third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The site may add advertising or other third-party services in the future. If
      those services change the information collected or how it is used, this policy
      will be updated.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      Question reports may be retained while they are reviewed and afterward as part
      of the quality-control history. Operational logs and analytics are retained
      according to the settings and limits of the service providers used by the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can close the browser tab to end the current session-storage workflow. You
      can also choose not to submit an optional question report. Browser and privacy
      controls may provide additional ways to limit local storage or analytics.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Cert Happens is a general educational resource and is not designed to collect
      personal information from children. The site does not knowingly request names,
      account details, or contact information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      This policy may be updated as the site adds features, advertising, or service
      providers. The date at the top of the page will show the latest revision.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <address>
      Privacy questions may be sent to
      <strong>{{ site.privacyAddress }}</strong>.
    </address>
